# README

# Demo QA Automation

Automation framework for [Demo QA](https://demoqa.com/) website using Selenium WebDriver, Cucumber (BDD), TestNG, and Maven.

---

## Project Structure


demo-qa-automation
├── src/main/java        # Utilities, drivers, base classes
├── src/main/resources   # Config files (properties, log4j, etc.)
├── src/test/java        # Step definitions, runners
├── src/test/resources   # Feature files, test data
├── pom.xml              # Maven dependencies & plugins
└── README.md            # Documentation



---

## Tech Stack
- Java 1.8+  
- Selenium WebDriver  
- Cucumber (BDD with Gherkin)  
- TestNG  
- Maven  

---

## How to Run
---bash
# Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/ajayverma401/demo-qa-automation.git
cd demo-qa-automation

# Install dependencies
mvn clean install

# Run tests
mvn test


Reports: `test-output/index.html`

---

## Features

* Page Object Model (POM)
* Cucumber BDD (feature files + step defs)
* Config-driven (URL, browser, timeout)
* Auto screenshot on failure and at each step
* Logging (Log4j)
* CI/CD ready (Jenkins, GitHub Actions)
* Cross-browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
* Data-driven (external test data support)
* Extent Reports

---

## Git Ignore

Excluded from repo:

* target/, test-output/, logs/, screenshots/
* IDE-specific files (.classpath, .project, .settings/, .idea/, *.iml)

